# ============================================================
# DETAIL CORE ARCHITECTURE
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: architecture
domain: detail
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

purpose:
Defines the core architecture principles of the detail domain.

scope:
The core architecture governs responsibility, boundary,
granularity, lifecycle, and consumption rules for all detail records.

design_intent:
CivilizationOS requires a canonical architectural place
for detailed truth that is more granular than the base model
but still stricter than presentation text.
The detail core exists to stop semantic drift and accidental duplication.

canonical_rules:
- Detail must not redefine the meaning of a core model.
- Detail must not directly own session runtime state.
- Detail must not directly own flow sequencing authority.
- Detail must not directly own screen implementation.
- Detail must always bind to a canonical target reference.
- Detail must always define visibility and lifecycle semantics.
- Detail must remain structured and machine-readable.

required_behavior:
- The system must distinguish core truth from refined detail truth.
- The system must reject detail records without canonical targets.
- The system must reject detail records that contradict core truth.
- The system must support stable consumption by runtime and interface layers.

state_model:
detail_record_state:
- draft
- reviewed
- canonical
- revised
- deprecated
- superseded

detail_visibility_scope:
- public
- internal
- restricted
- sealed

detail_lifecycle:
- proposed
- prepared
- active
- hidden
- archived

validation_rules:
- target_ref is required.
- detail_type is required.
- visibility_scope is required.
- lifecycle_state is required.
- contradictory override of core truth is prohibited.
- free-form unstructured payload without schema binding is prohibited.
- missing ownership or consumer scope is prohibited.

transition_rules:
- draft -> reviewed
- reviewed -> canonical
- canonical -> revised
- canonical -> deprecated
- deprecated -> superseded
- active -> hidden
- hidden -> archived

dependency:
depends_on:
- civilization core models
- meta classification and provenance
- world, story, player, and integration references

consumed_by:
- runtime detail loaders
- interface view builders
- flow support logic
- audit and trace tools

example_scenarios:
- A school exists as a world facility model.
  Its internal room semantics, operational notes,
  usage boundaries, and visibility tiers belong to detail.
- A player occupation exists as a player model.
  Its detailed working conditions and contextual explanation
  belong to detail.
